Me: Expresses how much nostalgia I have for the pre gen 5 Pokemon games that allowed you to see Pokemon in 3D.
Also Me:...
body:
Me: Expresses how much nostalgia I have for the pre gen 5 Pokemon games that allowed you to see Pokemon in 3D.

Also Me: Misspells Colosseum so damn hard that I wish that Tumblr was NOT run so incompetently so that way I could auto-update all reblogs with the edit, because Colosseum is my favourite Pokemon game and I hate how loads of people have forgotten it simply because of it being part of the most expensive generation in the series.

tags: you would not believe your eyes
summary: #96  Peekypeeky (Pk as in psychokinesis repeated. Also peek as in see) Psychic  The Lemur Pokémon  Ability: Keen Eye  Hidden...
caption:
#96  Peekypeeky (Pk as in psychokinesis repeated. Also peek as in see) Psychic  The Lemur Pokémon 

Ability: Keen Eye  Hidden Ability: Nocturnal   Stats: 50/50/40/70/50/70 Total: 330

Dex: This Pokémon’s eyes have the power to see into anybody’s mind, allowing them to read anyone’s mind. Their eyes can also see into the past and the future. 

Moveset: Scratch, Leer, Confusion, Spite, Fury Swipes, Psybeam, Mesmerize, Miracle Eye, Extrasensory 

Inspiration: Ring tailed lemurs 

Evolves into Psy-Aye at level 32

#97 Psy-Aye (Psychic + Aye-Aye)  Psychic  The Shaman Pokémon 

Ability: Necromancer  Hidden Ability: Nocturnal  Stats: 70/70/60/100/90/90 Total: 480

Dex: It gains the power to control spiritual powers upon evolution. Aboriginal Alumunoans commonly use Psy-Aye’s spiritual powers for healing and exorcising evil spirits out of possessed people. If a Psy-Aye points to somebody with it’s long bony finger, it’s because it saw that person’s future and that they’re going to die soon. 

Moveset: Psychic Terrain, Night Shade, Hex, Vengeance, Heal Pulse, Heal Block, Dark Pulse, Pain Split, Psychic, Future Sight, Memento

Inspiration: Aye-Ayes, shaman/witch doctors, the fact that the name lemur comes from the Latin word lemures, which refers to ghosts that were exorcised during ancient Rome. The eyes on it’s hands and the fact it has no eyes on it’s face is a reference to the Japanese yokai Tenome 

Necromancer- Boosts the power of the user’s ghost type moves by 50%

#97 Psy-Aye (Psychic + Aye-Aye)  Psychic  The Shaman Pokémon 

Ability: Necromancer  Hidden Ability: Nocturnal  Stats: 70/70/60/100/90/90 Total: 480

Dex: It gains the power to control spiritual powers upon evolution. Aboriginal Alumunoans commonly use Psy-Aye’s spiritual powers for healing and exorcising evil spirits out of possessed people. If a Psy-Aye points to somebody with it’s long bony finger, it’s because it saw that person’s future and that they’re going to die soon. 

Moveset: Psychic Terrain, Night Shade, Hex, Vengeance, Heal Pulse, Heal Block, Dark Pulse, Pain Split, Psychic, Future Sight, Memento

Inspiration: Aye-Ayes, shaman/witch doctors, the fact that the name lemur comes from the Latin word lemures, which refers to ghosts that were exorcised during ancient Rome. The eyes on it’s hands and the fact it has no eyes on it’s face is a reference to the Japanese yokai Tenome 

Necromancer- Boosts the power of the user’s ghost type moves by 50%
